results.name: Smallest number m greater than n such that the happy couples of m and n have a member in common.
comment: The intersection of {A007966(n),A007967(n)} and {A007966(a(n)),A007967(a(n))} is not empty, but the intersection of {A007966(n),A007967(n)} and {A007966(m),A007967(m)} is empty for n<m<a(n).
link: J. H. Conway, On Happy Factorizations, J. Integer Sequences, Vol. 1, 1998, #1.
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jun 19 2011
